  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db8\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0dbb\u0dd1 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel prices rise overnight",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ceylon Petroleum Corporation and the Ceylon Indian Oil Company (IOC) have increased fuel prices with effect from this morning (26).",
        "Accordingly, a liter of 92 octane petrol which was Rs. 420 was priced at Rs. 50, a liter of 95 octane petrol which was Rs. 450 was priced at Rs. 100, a liter of auto diesel which was Rs. The price of a liter of diesel has also been increased by 75 rupees.",
        "With this price increase, a liter of 92 octane petrol will cost Rs. 470, a liter of 95 octane petrol Rs. 550, a liter of auto diesel Rs. 460 and a liter of premium diesel Rs. 520."
      ],
